Detailed Description

The BtAvrcpNotificationMessage is sent in order to inform the application programmer of an incoming connect or disconnect. The parameters for connect (a so called stack, or btapi handle) is held as a parameter (stack message argument). The btapi handle has to be sent back to the stack, using an implementation of the BtAvrcpOperationService using the method ConnectResponse. In case of an incoming connect the application programmer needs to create a new instance of its BtAvrcpOperationServiceImpl. If this succeeds, one uses the instance to answer the incoming connect. In case of a disconnect notification the respective instance, which is passed in the Disconnect notification, has to be destroyed.
